mash ton, hot liquor tank, and brew kettle.

00:01:15.190 --> 00:01:19.860
And we keep it nice and dirty 'cause we kind
of like the look of that, that tarnished copper.

00:01:19.860 --> 00:01:24.280
Maybe clean it once a year or so. This system's
kind of designed to make lager beer. That's,

00:01:24.280 --> 00:01:28.000
that's what we love around here, so that's
what we do.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.500
It seems like right now in America, German
beer is getting more popular. What do you

00:01:32.500 --> 00:01:35.820
think is the reason for that? What makes it
so popular right now?

00:01:35.820 --> 00:01:43.160
Um, I don't know. It's, well one, it's one
of the untouched niches that - Okay. - are out there.

00:01:43.160 --> 00:01:48.240
Two, it's just, you know, it's
the subtle simplicity, I guess you could say

00:01:48.240 --> 00:01:53.660
of German beer. It's just really simple, straight
forward, easy drinking, sessiony, you know.

00:01:53.670 --> 00:01:58.950
I think in the past, Americans only really
got imported German beer. - Uh-huh.

00:01:58.950 --> 00:02:05.740
