different world. - Gotcha. Gotcha.

00:02:10.040 --> 00:02:15.080
These tanks right here are kind of special.
You don't see those too much in American breweries.

00:02:15.080 --> 00:02:20.760
They're horizontal lagering tanks, and they're
designed to help produce those lager beers.

00:02:20.760 --> 00:02:25.500
So they lay on the side because it helps allow
more contact with the yeast with the beer,

00:02:25.510 --> 00:02:29.940
and helps that long maturation phase lager beers need.

00:02:29.940 --> 00:02:34.580
How long does it take for the beer to go from
start to finish, coming out the tap?

00:02:34.580 --> 00:02:39.260
Um, good question. So, it's kind of based
on the strength of the beer. - Okay.

00:02:39.260 --> 00:02:44.740
Most of our, like, our sessiony weight beers like Pilsner
or Helles are about six weeks. - Okay.

00:02:44.740 --> 00:02:49.540
And then if we're getting into, like, Doppelbock
or Märzen or something like that, it's, it

00:02:49.540 --> 00:02:50.900
can be eight to twelve weeks.

00:02:50.900 --> 00:02:56.180
